{
  "texts": [
    "BERT (1 phase) represents the model in which only 400 annotated articles were used for fine-tuning.",
    "The performance of BERT-based NER in Phase I was validated by comparing it with different biomedical text mining tools such as PTC, Hunflaire [47], BERN and BERN2 (Supplementary Stable 3).",
    "It is obvious that the F1-scores of BERT (2 phases) to predict gene, variant, disease and species are 97.28%, 93.52%, 92.54% and 95.76%, which are improved by 0.77%, 2.46%, 0.56% and 1.54% upon the corresponding F1-scores of BERT (1 phase), 96.51%, 91.06%, 91.98% and 94.21%, respectively.",
    "This observation suggests that BERT-based NER with two phases in the finetuning step outperforms the one with only one phase.",
    "The 2.46% F1-score increase for variant is particularly important because of the critical role that variants usually play in the interpretation of genetic diseases."
  ]
}